Description: un convertidor binario que convierte binario en texto
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, New England, Northeastern US
Full Description: Un traductor binario es una aplicación de software o biblioteca que ayuda a convertir el código binario de un programa de computadora en un lenguaje de programación diferente (código fuente). A veces también se lo conoce como un convertidor de bytecode a código de máquina. El propósito del traductor binario es facilitar el desarrollo, la implementación y la ejecución de un programa de software en un lenguaje de programación diferente al convertirlo al código fuente que se puede interpretar y ejecutar en la plataforma de destino. Description: Improving public and private education throughout the United States.
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, Southern US
Full Description: The Hawkins-Stafford Education Improvement Amendments of 1988 (Public Law 100-297) established the National Cooperative Education Statistics System. This responsibility is retained under the Education Science Reform Act of 2002, which gives NCES authority to establish a cooperative system that would "produce and maintain, with the cooperation of the states, comparable and uniform education statistics." To assist in meeting the mandate, NCES established the National Forum on Education Statistics (Forum). The Forum is a voluntary, democratic, participative, and cooperative federal-state-local body with a mission to plan, develop and recommend education data resources that will support local, state, and national efforts to improve public and private education throughout the United States. The Forum is comprised of representatives from state and local education agencies (appointed by their state's superintendent), the federal government, and other organizations with an interest in education data. Forum members work collaboratively to address problems, identify best practices, develop resources, and consider new approaches to improving data collection and utility, all while remaining sensitive to privacy concerns and administrative burden. All Forum publications and resources are free of charge and can be accessed through this website, along with detailed information about the organization, upcoming events, and other resources related to education data.
Industry Groups: Content and Publishing, Education, Government and Military, Media and Entertainment

Description: Entrepreneurial companies are the source of nearly all net new jobs and most of the new wealth created in the economy – wealth which helps
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: Entrepreneurial companies are the source of nearly all net new jobs and most of the new wealth created in the economy – wealth which helps fund civic projects and services as the seed capital for the next generation of growth companies.  Entrepreneurship is a critical part of a sound economic development strategy since communities that wish to create jobs and wealth must have a healthy supply of home-grown entrepreneurial companies.  Therefore, with the publication of the 1996 Growing Success: A Report on Entrepreneurship in Louisville, the report called for the formation of the ENTERPRISECORP.  The intent was for the ENTERPRISECORP to be the focal point for the community’s entrepreneurial development effort.  It called for the ENTERPRISECORP to create a new culture of entrepreneurship in Louisville and to increase dramatically the number and quality of entrepreneurial companies in Louisville.  The Report also indicated the consolidation and coordination of existing entrepreneurial support programs, the launch of significant new programs, and becoming a virtual incubator and champion for the cause of entrepreneurship. And so in 1999, the ENTERPRISECORP was formed.  Today we are the entrepreneurial arm of Greater Louisville Inc. – the metro chamber of commerce -- supported by our partners and board of advisors, and serving a community of early stage and fast growth businesses with the pursuit that Greater Louisville becomes a more prosperous, dynamic and resilient region.

Full Description: North by South (NXS) brings open source technology integration to companies using the experience of a unique Developers Network comprised of US & Latin American free software specialists. From a hub in SÃ£o Paulo, Brazil, this San Francisco team is augmented by the experience of open source developers who have participated in the world's largest regional migration to free software. Beginning with Brazilian President "Lula" da Silva's decree to migrate all public agencies and state-owned firms to free software, a wave of open source adoption has swept across Latin America: from Brazil to Ecuador to Argentina to Venezuela to Paraguay, governments across the region have made a deliberate and aggressive migration to open source technologies, with incredible success. North by South's experience in this process, combined with their management team's experience in San Francisco's dot-com booms, has positioned NXS as a company able to provide planning & implementation for businesses who want to leverage the advantages of open source technology in their organizations. NXS is one of the first companies to provide near-shoring to Latin America.
